quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Appending to a File[/h1]

Let's create an example of a form that adds filled-in data to a file.[code format="php"]<?php
if(isset($_POST['text'])) {
  $name = $_POST['text'];
  $handle = fopen('names.txt', 'a');
  fwrite($handle, $name."\n");
  fclose($handle); 
}
?>
<form method="post">
  Name: <input type="text" name="text" /> 
  <input type="submit" name="submit" />
</form>[/code]
Now, each time a name is entered and submitted, it's added to the "names.txt" file, along with a new line.

The [b]isset()[/b] function determined whether the form had been submitted, as well as whether the text contained a value.
[note]We did not specify an [b]action[/b] attribute for the form, so it will submit to itself.[/note]
